# Python Code Style

## Required
- Follow PEP 8 with a practical max line length of 88.
- Add type hints for all function parameters and return values.
- Add Google-style docstrings for public functions, methods, and classes.

## Implementation Preferences
- Use meaningful names instead of short abbreviations.
- Favor small, composable functions over long procedural blocks.
- Keep side effects explicit at function boundaries.
